  <div class="badge"><span class="status-dot"></span>Open Source · MIT License</div>
  <h1 class="title">One <span>.NET Language Server</span>. Every Editor.</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    SharpLsp is an open-source C# and F# language server built in Rust. Full Roslyn-powered IntelliSense,
    diagnostics, go-to-definition, and refactoring — in VS Code, Zed, or any LSP-compatible editor.
  </p>
  <div class="button-row">
    <a class="button button-primary" href="/docs/">Get Started</a>
    <a class="button button-secondary" href="https://github.com/Nimblesite/SharpLsp">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined" aria-hidden="true">code</span>
      View on GitHub
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="panel">
  <div class="card-grid card-grid-three">
    <article class="feature-card">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined icon-box" aria-hidden="true">terminal</span>
      <h2>VS Code &amp; Zed Support</h2>
      <p>Full Roslyn completions, diagnostics, go-to-definition, and inlay hints. Neovim, Helix, and Emacs support coming soon.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-card">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined icon-box" aria-hidden="true">functions</span>
      <h2>F# as a First-Class Citizen</h2>
      <p>F# language server backed by FSharp.Compiler.Service. The same feature depth as C# — not an afterthought.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-card">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined icon-box" aria-hidden="true">lock_open</span>
      <h2>No Subscriptions. No Lock-in.</h2>
      <p>MIT licensed. Works in VSCodium, Open VSX, and any LSP-compatible editor. No Microsoft account required.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

